# Android/iOS specific ignores live in `android/.gitignore` and
# `ios/App/.gitignore` (generated by `cap add android` / `cap add ios`).
# Here we cover only shell-level outputs that do not belong to a native
# project sub-tree.
#
# NOTE: `apps/mobile-shell/ios/` is intentionally NOT committed at all.
# `cap add ios` needs Xcode + CocoaPods on macOS, and both the PR-time
# workflow (`.github/workflows/mobile-shell-ios.yml`) and the release
# workflow (`.github/workflows/mobile-shell-ios-release.yml`) regenerate
# the directory on `macos-latest` and cache Pods via `actions/cache`.
# See `apps/mobile-shell/README.md` → "iOS" and `MOBILE.md` → "Release — iOS".

# Capacitor CLI scratch directories
www/
dist/

# iOS build outputs (if `cap add ios` was run on a macOS checkout)
ios/App/build/
ios/App/Pods/
ios/App/App/public/
ios/DerivedData/
